	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Gilles Fauconnier</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><div class="fn" style="display:inline">Gilles Fauconnier</div></th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Gilles Fauconnier.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg/220px-Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="249" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg/330px-Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg/440px-Gilles_Fauconnier.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1450" data-file-height="1638" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Born</th><td><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1944-08-19">19 August 1944</span><span style="display:none">&#160;(<span class="dtstart bday">1944-08-19</span>)</span> (age&#160;<span class="currentage"></span>74)</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Nationality</th><td class="category">French</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Fields</th><td class="category"><a href="/wiki/Cognitive_science" title="Cognitive science">cognitive science</a>, <a href="/wiki/Linguistics" title="Linguistics">linguistics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Institutions</th><td><a href="/wiki/UC_San_Diego" class="mw-redirect" title="UC San Diego">UC San Diego</a></td></tr><tr style="display:none"><td colspan="2">
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Gilles Fauconnier</b> (<small>French pronunciation:&#160;&#8203;</small><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/French" title="Help:IPA/French">[ʒil fokɔˈnje]</a></span>) (born 19 August 1944) is a French <a href="/wiki/Linguistics" title="Linguistics">linguist</a>, researcher in <a href="/wiki/Cognitive_science" title="Cognitive science">cognitive science</a>, and author,<sup id="cite_ref-HL_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HL-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-LZ_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-LZ-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> currently working in the U.S.  He is a professor at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_California,_San_Diego" title="University of California, San Diego">University of California, San Diego</a>, in the Department of Cognitive Science.
</p><p>His work with <a href="/wiki/Mark_Turner_(cognitive_scientist)" title="Mark Turner (cognitive scientist)">Mark Turner</a> founded the theory of <a href="/wiki/Conceptual_blending" title="Conceptual blending">conceptual blending</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-LZ_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-LZ-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>His books include:
</p>
<ul><li><i>The Way We Think: Conceptual Blending and the Mind's Hidden Complexities</i> (with Mark Turner) (2003)<sup id="cite_ref-BG1_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BG1-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>
<li><i>Conceptual Integration Networks (1998)</i> (with Mark Turner)</li>
<li><i>Mappings in Thought and Language</i> (1997)<sup id="cite_ref-BG2_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BG2-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>
<li><i>Mental spaces: Aspects of meaning construction in natural language</i> (1994)</li></ul>
